  <h2 id="spacing-scale">The responsive spacing scales</h2>
  <p>We use Figma-aligned spacing size keys instead of the older point-based scale. Use the size key itself in utility classes and responsive mixins, for example <code>ofh-u-margin-56</code> or <code>@include ofh-responsive-padding(40)</code>.</p>
  <p>The responsive scales are split by direction. When you use the mixin with <code>all</code>, top and bottom use the vertical scale, while left and right use the horizontal scale.</p>

